Virginia McKenna https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Virginia_McKenna 0 Virginia Anne McKenna, OBE (born 7 June 1931) is a British stage and screen actress, author and wildlife campaigner. She is best known for the films A Town Like Alice (1958), Carve Her Name with Pride (1958) and Born Free (1966), Ring of Bright Water (1969) and for her long collaboration with husband Bill Travers.
